    cellular: "Benzodiazepines enhance GABA activity by increasing chloride channel opening frequency. Common medications: alprazolam, lorazepam, diazepam, clonazepam. Physical dependence develops with regular use beyond 2-4 weeks. Withdrawal can be life-threatening (seizures, delirium), similar to alcohol withdrawal. Withdrawal must be medically managed with gradual tapering over weeks to months. Symptoms include anxiety, insomnia, tremor, sweating, and sensory hypersensitivity. Protracted withdrawal can last months. Combined benzodiazepine-opioid use dramatically increases overdose risk. Counselors support patients through the tapering process, addressing underlying anxiety and developing alternative coping strategies.",
