    cellular: "CBT for addiction identifies and modifies thoughts and behaviors maintaining substance use. Functional analysis examines antecedents (triggers), behavior (substance use), and consequences (reinforcement). High-risk situations are identified and alternative coping strategies developed. Cognitive restructuring addresses permission-giving thoughts, minimizing, and rationalizing. Skills training includes drug refusal skills, assertiveness, problem-solving, and pleasant activity scheduling. Relapse prevention (Marlatt) distinguishes lapse (single use) from relapse (return to pattern), addressing the abstinence violation effect (all-or-nothing thinking after a lapse). Coping skills include urge management (urge surfing), thought stopping, and behavioral substitution.",
