    cellular: "Technology-based interventions expand addiction treatment access and effectiveness. mHealth applications support recovery with tracking tools, coping skill reminders, and community connections. reSET and reSET-O are FDA-cleared digital therapeutics for SUD and OUD. Telehealth counseling improves access for rural and underserved populations, with COVID-19 regulatory changes expanding MAT prescribing flexibility. Computerized CBT programs deliver evidence-based content with reduced therapist burden. Recovery support apps provide meeting finders, sobriety tracking, and peer support. Considerations include digital literacy, access barriers (smartphone, internet), privacy/security, and maintaining therapeutic relationship quality through technology.",
